Cymbopogon martini var. sofia

   [5125.jpg]
    Authority   (Roxb.) J.F. Watson
      Family    Liliopsida:Commelinidae:Cyperales:Gramineae
     Synonyms
   Common names
      Editor
   Ecocrop code 5125

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION A densely growing grass reaching a height of up to 2
   m. USES An essential oil is extracted from the flowering tops and
   mainly used in cheap perfumes. GROWING PERIOD Perennial grass. COMMON
   NAMES Rosha grass v. sofia, Palmarosa. FURTHER INF Rosha grass v. sofia
   grows wild in India. It can be found growing densely and abundantly at
   lower altitudes. Mentioned as a useful agroforestry species.

   Sources
   SOURCES (C. martini (Roxb.) Wats. var. sofia)
   Purseglove J 1972 pp 140 [DRA, RAIN, USE]
   Roecklein J 1987 pp 102 [USE]
   Duke J 1975 pp 14 [PH, RAIN, TEMP]
   Nair P 1980 pp 314 [DRA, RAIN, FER, USE, LIG]

